You are not invoking `handleClick` when you press the button.

```
onClick={() =&gt; this.handleClick}
```

is equivalent to

```
onClick={() =&gt; {
  return this.handleClick
}}
```

which is not the same as 

```
onClick={() =&gt; {
  return this.handleClick(/* do you need to pass a number here? */)
}}
```

or

```
onClick={this.handleClick}
```

Your click handler is not being called, you would want to change your code like 

     &lt;button className=&quot;nextButton&quot; onClick={() =&gt; this.handleClick()}&gt;Next &lt;/button&gt;

If you want to increment state by one every time you click, you would do so,

     handleClick = () =&gt; {
        this.setState((state) =&gt; { nextPage: state.nextPage + 1 })
     }

Here we are passing updater to setState because react batches the state updates, so if you directly access it, it may not be correct

Hope it helps

