&gt; I have to send only 1 class to the teacher, which means I can&#39;t import another class into the first class which would contain those object (unless that&#39;s not what you where trying to explain.

1.  You can declare a class *inside* another class.  For example:

        public class Homework {
            private static class Car {
                ...
            }
            private static class Reservation {
                ...
            }
        }

2.  You can put two or more classes in a single source code file, provided that they are all in the same package, and only one of them is declared as `public`.

So this means that your requirement to submit only one file does not prevent you from writing your code in an object-oriented fashion.

